variable
	is used to store data
datatype
	is what kind of value variable is holding
	5 types of datatypes
	number - int, float, complex
	bool - true false
	dictionary - key value pair
	sequence- tuple, list, string
	set - {}

		int - used to store the whole number without decimal(+ve, -ve)
		float - used to store the decimal numbers
		complex - used to store imaginary numbers

		tuple - used to store multiple data of different datatypes, it is immutable (can not be changed after creation) (unordered)
		list - used to store multiple data of different datatypes, it is mutable means we can change the data at particular index
		string- used to store a-z values strings are immutable

		set - is a collection of unique items that are unordered and do not allow duplicates, when we print the set duplicates are automatically removed(unordered)
		dictionary - is a collection of key value pairs in which keys must be unique, values can be fetched by its key(ordered)
operators
	6
	arithmetic { + - * / %) -
	comparison {< > <= >= != ==}
	assignment { = }
	identity {is, is not}
		this operator checks for the location of the variable, used to check if two variables are same object in memory or not
	logical <and or not>
	membership <in, not in>
		used to check if the value is available in the collection or not

conditional Statement
	IF  - checks condition if true if blocks executes otherwise program is terminated
	ELIF - if first condition is false, elif block executes and checks another condition if elif condition is true than elif block executes other wise jumps to next step if any
	ELSE - if none of the condition is executes then else block executes
loop
	loop is used to repeat the block of code multiple times OR loop is a way to run code again and again automatically until condition becomes false
	entry <for and while>
	exit do while
	for loop is used when we know how many times we want to execute the code
	while loop is used when we are unsure how many times we want to execute the code

	reduce code redundancy, saves time
function
	is a block of code which executes tasks and can be reusable
	4 types of argument
	    positional
	    keywise
	    length (can assign multiple values in a single arguments using *)
	    default
lambda
	is a small function without name OR
	is a reusable block of code which have single expression and can have multiple arguments
module
	module is a file that contains code such as class, function, variables, which we can reuse in other program or files
	2 types
	user define
	built in
	there are external modules as well which we can install
exception handling
	exception handling is a way to handle errors so the program doesnt crash and executes till the end
	OR
	exception handling is a method to detect and handle the error so that program runs smoothly without crashing

	try - code which may cause error
	except - handles error
	else - runs if no any error occurs
	finally - runs always no matter if error occurred or not
file handling
	file handling means to work with the file such as creating, updating, deleting, reading
	saves data
	reads data
	updates data
	deletes data
python to JSON and Vice versa
    dump() writes data in json file
    dumps() json serialize (converts to JSON string)

    load()
    loads()